{"name": "youtube-search", "metadata": {"name": "youtube-search", "version": "2.1.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "home_page": "https://github.com/joetats/youtube_search", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": "Perform YouTube video searches without the API", "upload_time": 1664934462}, "documentation": ["# youtube_search\n\nPython function for searching for youtube videos to avoid using their heavily rate-limited API\n\nTo avoid using the API, this uses the form on the youtube homepage and scrapes the resulting page.\n\n## Example Usage\n\nFor a basic search (and all of the current functionality), you can use the search tool as follows:\n\n```pip install youtube-search```\n\n```python\nfrom youtube_search import YoutubeSearch\n\nresults = YoutubeSearch('search terms', max_results=10).to_json()\n\nprint(results)\n\n# returns a json string\n\n########################################\n\nresults = YoutubeSearch('search terms', max_results=10).to_dict()\n\nprint(results)\n# returns a dictionary\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "youtube_search", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "youtube_search.YoutubeSearch", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "youtube_search.YoutubeSearch.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "search_terms", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "max_results", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "youtube_search.YoutubeSearch._search", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "youtube_search.YoutubeSearch._parse_html", "asynchronous"